titleInfo.title: Letter to John Wedderburn, Accountant General in Bombay, from Robert Money, Assistant to the Resident

physicalDescription.extent: The letter has been struck through in blue pencil.

mods.abstract: The letter is a covering letter, enclosing three abstracts from the assistant surgeon at the Residency, for the Resident's disbursements, totalling 599 rupees, sent by Money in the present absence of Stannus from the Residency.
